title: Vanessa Hudgens stylish in dungarees and camel jacket

text:
She's the ultimate queen of bohemian style.
And Vanessa Hudgens rocked another chic ensemble as she grabbed a spot of breakfast in Los Angeles on Thursday morning.
The actress, 28, looked effortlessly on-trend in a pair of denim dungarees and a camel corduroy jacket with a cream fur-effect collar.
Scroll down for video
Boho queen: Vanessa Hudgens rocked another chic bohemian-inspired ensemble as she grabbed a spot of breakfast in Los Angeles on Thursday morning
Teetering along in a pair of towering black peep-toe heels, the former High School Musical star teamed her turned-up denims with a simple white crop top.
The brunette wore her dark locks slicked back into a tight bun and accentuated her striking features with vampy berry lipstick.
Vanessa toted her belongings in a large chocolate brown leather Chloe handbag, while sheltering her eyes from the Californian sun with a pair of stylish aviator shades.
Caffeine fix: The actress, 28, looked effortlessly on-trend in a pair of denim dungarees and a camel corduroy jacket with a cream fur-effect collar
The actress grabbed a healthy breakfast on the go, and was seen emerging from her eatery of choice with a refreshing iced coffee and a bowl of fruit and yoghurt.
Vanessa - who currently has a role in NBC's new show Powerless, set in the Marvel world - has some existing projects in the works.
The star has bagged herself a role in forthcoming film, The Prenup, which will start filming in the next couple of months.
Vanessa will join Lone Survivor actor Emile Hirsch in the new romantic comedy.
Dressed to impress: Teetering along in a pair of towering black peep-toe heels, the former High School Musical star teamed her turned-up denims with a simple white crop top
The plot of the film centres around the aftermath of an American investment banker suggesting to his British bride that they should get a pre-nuptial agreement the night before their wedding.
Downton Abbey's Hugh Bonneville will play Emile's character's father in the feel-good chick flick.
Vanessa's personal life seems to be going just as well as her career.
The actress - who previously dated Zac Efron, 29, for five years - has been in a long-term relationship with actor and singer Austin Butler, 25, since 2011.
